In Azure Functions, the `ServiceBusTrigger` input does not have a built-in `SessionId` property. However, you can access the session ID from the `ServiceBusMessages` properties. Here is how you can do it:

```csharp
[FunctionName("ProcessMessage")]
public static void Run(
    [ServiceBusTrigger("queueName", Connection = "ServiceBusConnection")]  
      ServiceBusMessage msg, 
      ServiceBusHeaderSettings settings, 
      FunctionContext context, 
      ILogger logger)
{
    logger.LogInformation($"C# ServiceBus queue trigger processed message: {msg.Body}");

    Guid messageId = Guid.NewGuid();
    Guid? sessionId = msg.Properties.TryGetValue("SessionId", out object itemId) && itemId!= null? (Guid?)itemId : (Guid?)settings.SessionId;

    logger.LogInformation($"Message ID: {msg.MessageId}, Session ID: {sessionId}");
}
```
In the `ServiceBusTrigger`, the `SessionId` is passed as a `ServiceBusHeaderSettings` property. You can also get it from the `ServiceBusMessageProperties`, but it requires specifying it when sending the message from the sender.

```csharp
Guid sessionId = Guid.NewGuid();
ServiceBusMessage message = new ServiceBusMessage("Hello, World!");
message.Headers.Add("SessionId", sessionId);
```
You may want to access it through the `ServiceBusTrigger` and iterate through the messages in the batch, as in Azure Functions, the Service Bus trigger is a receiving point for Service Bus messages and can be a collection of messages.

```csharp
[FunctionName("ProcessMessageBatch")]
public static void Run(
    [ServiceBusTrigger("queueName", Connection = "ServiceBusConnection", IsProcessSession = true)]  
    ProcessServiceBusMessage[] messages,
    FunctionContext context,
    ILogger logger)
{
    foreach(ProcessServiceBusMessage item in messages)
    {
        logger.LogInformation($"C# ServiceBus queue trigger processed message: {item.Message.Body}, Session ID: {item.Message.Properties.TryGetValue("SessionId", out object sessionIdItem) && sessionIdItem!= null? (Guid?)sessionIdItem : (Guid?)item.Message.Headers.Get("SessionId")}");
    }
}
```

