Metaprogramming is a programming technique that involves writing code that can manipulate or generate other code at runtime. In PHP, metaprogramming is achieved using various techniques, including reflection, caching, and code generation.

**Reflection in PHP**

Reflection allows a program to inspect its own structure and behavior at runtime. In PHP, the `ReflectionClass` and `ReflectionFunction` classes provide methods to access and manipulate class and function metadata.

Example:
```php
// Define a class
class Person {
    public $name;
    public $age;

    function __construct($name, $age) {
        $this->name = $name;
        $this->age = $age;
    }

    function printInfo() {
        echo "Name: $this->name, Age: $this->age\n";
    }
}

// Use reflection to get class metadata
$reflect = new ReflectionClass('Person');
echo "Class Name: ". $reflect->getName(). "\n";

// Get method metadata
$printInfo = $reflect->getMethod('printInfo');
echo "Method: ". $printInfo->getName(). "\n";

// Invoke the method using reflection
$person = new Person('John Doe', 30);
$printInfo->invoke($person);
```
**Using Reflection to Set and Get Object Properties**

```php
// Define a class
class Person {
    private $privateProperty;
    public $publicProperty;

    public function __construct() {
        $this->privateProperty = 'Private Value';
        $this->publicProperty = 'Public Value';
    }

    public function getPrivateProperty() {
        return $this->privateProperty;
    }

    public function setPrivateProperty($value) {
        $this->privateProperty = $value;
    }
}

// Use reflection to set and get object properties
$person = new Person();

// Get public property value using reflection
$reflect = new ReflectionClass('Person');
$publicProperty = $reflect->getProperty('publicProperty');
$publicProperty->setAccessible(true);
echo "Public Property Value: ". $publicProperty->getValue($person). "\n";

// Set private property value using reflection
$privateProperty = $reflect->getProperty('privateProperty');
$privateProperty->setAccessible(true);
$privateProperty->setValue($person, 'New Private Value');
echo "Private Property Value: ". $privateProperty->getValue($person). "\n";
```
