COBS Finite State Machine FIFO Module
=====================================

Overview
--------

The COBS (Consistent-Overhead Byte Stuffing) finite state machine (FSM) FIFO module is a C++ implementation of a COBS-encoded FIFO (First-In-First-Out) buffer.

COBS is a widely-used protocol used to efficiently send variable-length data over a limited-memory or serial communication link. The module implements the COBS FSM to efficiently encode and decode the input data.

Installation
------------

To use the COBS_FIFO module, simply include the `COBS_FIFO.h` header file in your C++ project:

```cpp
#include <COBS_FIFO.h>
```

Usage
-----

To use the COBS_FIFO module, follow these steps:

1.  Create a COBS_FIFO object, passing in the maximum size of the FIFO buffer:

    ```cpp
COBS_FIFO fifo(1024);
```

2.  Write data to the FIFO using the `write` method:

    ```cpp
fifo.write(data, len);
```

3.  Read data from the FIFO using the `read` method:

    ```cpp
uint8_t *readBuff = new uint8_t[fifo.size()];
uint16_t readLen = fifo.read(readBuff);
```

4.  Destroy the FIFO object when you're done using it:

    ```cpp
delete readBuff;
fifo.destroy();
```

Example Code
------------

Here's a simple example of how to use the COBS_FIFO module:

```cpp
#include <COBS_FIFO.h>
#include <iostream>

int main() {
    // Create a COBS_FIFO object with a maximum size of 1024 bytes
    COBS_FIFO fifo(1024);

    // Set up some example data
    uint8_t data[] = "Hello, world!";
    uint16_t len = strlen((char *)data);

    // Write the data to the FIFO
    fifo.write(data, len);

    // Create a buffer to store the read data
    uint8_t *readBuff = new uint8_t[fifo.size()];

    // Read the data from the FIFO
    uint16_t readLen = fifo.read(readBuff);

    // Print out the read data
    std::cout << "Read: ";
    for (uint16_t i = 0; i < readLen; i++) {
        std::cout << (int)readBuff[i];
    }
    std::cout << std::endl;

    delete readBuff;

